## CHI-30 `middleware/wrap_writer.go` — Findings

### BUG (High) — Line 209: Double-counting bytes in `ReadFrom` tee path

`httpFancyWriter.ReadFrom` does `io.Copy(&f.basicWriter, r)`, which calls `basicWriter.Write()` for each chunk — incrementing `b.bytes` at line 109 on every call. After `io.Copy` returns, line 209 then adds the total `n` bytes again. `BytesWritten()` returns 2× the actual bytes transferred whenever `tee != nil` and `ReadFrom` is the write path.

The non-tee path (lines 212–216) is correct because `rf.ReadFrom` bypasses `basicWriter.Write()` entirely.

### BUG (Low) — Lines 9 & 107: Deprecated `io/ioutil`

Imports `"io/ioutil"` and uses `ioutil.Discard.Write(buf)` at line 107. The main branch already removed all other `ioutil` uses (commit `a36a925`); this file was missed. Should be `io.Discard`.

### QUESTION (Low) — Lines 144, 169, 191, 232: `Flush()` sets `wroteHeader = true` without setting `code`

All `Flush()` implementations set `wroteHeader = true` but never set `b.code`. If `Flush()` is called before any `Write()`/`WriteHeader()`, `Status()` returns `0` even though the underlying writer sends an implicit 200. Unclear if intentional.
